sentences: With the addition of Dean Webb (mandolin) and Mitch Jayne (bass), they formed The Dillards in 1962.
Along with Denver Pyle and Margaret Ann Peterson, they were the Darlings of Mayberry from 1963 to 1966.
In 1968, Doug left the Dillards and joined the Byrds for their first European tour.
In 1966, Doug and Rodney Dillard provided music for the film Bonnie and Clyde.
This recording earned four Grammy awards in 1968.
In 1969, Doug recorded the Banjo Album, followed by other solo projects.
In 1982, he launched the Doug Dillard Band.
The Dillards briefly reunited in 1986 to appear on the TV movie Return to Mayberry.
In 1989, Dillard's album Heartbreak Hotel was nominated by the Recording Academy for the Grammy award for Best Bluegrass Recording.
In 2009, the Dillards were inducted into the Bluegrass Hall of Fame by the International Bluegrass Music Association (IBMA).
Dillard was inducted individually into the Society for the Preservation of Bluegrass Music of America (SPBGMA) Preservation Hall of Greats in 1992.
